## Signature lenses (the value-generation angles)

> Your signature lenses are the small set (≈4-6) of repeatable angles you see the world through — the
> reason your take on a topic is *yours* and not the obvious one. The writing skills
> (`commenting-others`, `respond-to-own`, `post`, `dm-sales-coach`) run drafts through them to satisfy
> the "lived experience OR signature lens" rule, and rotate a different lens per variation
> (angle-diversity). Derive 4-6 from your own framework, scorecard, or core point of view — never a
> generic list. Each lens is a *question you ask of any post*; the answer is your distinctive add.
> `/onboard` (Step 2c) fills these.

1. **[ xxx — lens name / theme ]**
   [ xxx — 1-2 sentence description, in your words ]
   **Use as a lens:** [ xxx — the question to run a draft through ]
   *Framework tie: [ xxx ]. Powers: [ xxx — which content theme/day ].*

2. **[ xxx ]** — repeat for 4-6 lenses.

